{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"ImageDecoding-Protocol","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"ImageDecoding Protocol"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"At the core of the decoding infrastructure is the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageDecoding"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["public protocol ImageDecoding {","    \/\/\/ Produces an image from the given image data.","    func decode(_ data: Data) -> ImageContainer?","","    \/\/\/ Produces an image from the given partially downloaded image data.","    \/\/\/ This method might be called multiple times during a single decoding","    \/\/\/ session. When the image download is complete, `decode(data:)` method is called.","    \/\/\/","    \/\/\/ - returns: nil by default.","    func decodePartiallyDownloadedData(_ data: Data) -> ImageContainer?","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageContainer"},{"type":"text","text":" is a struct that wraps the decoded image itself along with (optionally) the original data and some additional information. The decoder decides what to attach to the container."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["public struct ImageContainer {","    \/\/ Either `UIImage` or `NSImage` depending on the platform.","    public let image: UIImage","    public let data: Data?","    public let userInfo: [AnyHashable: Any]","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When the first chunk of the image data is loaded, "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImagePipeline"},{"type":"text","text":" creates a decoder for the given image format."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The pipeline uses "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageDecoderRegistry"},{"type":"text","text":" to find the decoder.  The decoder is created once and is reused across a single image decoding session until the final chunk of data is downloaded. If the decoder supports progressive decoding, make it a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"type":"text","text":" to retain state within a single decoding session."}]},{"style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageDecoding\/decode(_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" method only passes "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"data"},{"type":"text","text":" to the decoder. If the decoder needs additional information, pass it when instantiating it. "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageDecodingContext"},{"type":"text","text":" provides everything that you might need."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can also take advantage of "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageRequest\/userInfo"},{"type":"text","text":". For example, you may pass the target image view size to the SVG decoder to let it know the size of the image to create."}]}],"type":"aside","name":"Note"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The decoding is performed in the background on the operation queue provided in "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImagePipeline\/Configuration-swift.struct"},{"type":"text","text":". There is always only one decoding request at a time. The pipeline doesn’t call "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageDecoding\/decodePartiallyDownloadedData(_:)-9budu"},{"type":"text","text":" again until you are finished with the previous chunk."}]},{"anchor":"Registering-Decoders","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Registering Decoders"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To register the decoders, use "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageDecoderRegistry"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["func register() {","    ImageDecoderRegistry.shared.register(ImageDecoders.SVG.init)","}","","extension ImageDecoders {","    final class SVG: ImageDecoding {","        init?(context: ImageDecodingContext) {","            guard context.isCompleted else {","                return nil \/\/ No progressive decoding","            }","","            let isSVG = context.urlResponse?.url?.absoluteString.hasSuffix(\".svg\") ?? false","            guard isSVG else {","                return nil \/\/ Image format isn't supported.","            }   ","        }","    }","}"]},{"style":"tip","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To determine image type, use an "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/AssetType"},{"type":"text","text":" initializer that takes data as input. "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/AssetType"},{"type":"text","text":" represents uniform type identifiers or UTI."}]}],"type":"aside","name":"Tip"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When you register a decoder, you have access to "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageDecodingContext"},{"type":"text","text":" for the given decoding session."}]},{"anchor":"Rendering-Engines","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Rendering Engines"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The decoders in Nuke work at download time - regular decoders produce images as data arrives, while progressive decoders can produce multiple previews before delivering the final images. There are, however, scenarios when decoding at download time doesn’t work: for example, for animated images."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For animated images, it is not feasible to decode all of the frames and put them in memory as bitmaps at download time – it will consume too much memory. You have to postpone decoding to rendering time. When the image is displayed, a rendering engine, like "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/kaishin\/Gifu"},{"type":"text","text":" or others, will decode and cache image frames on demand."}]},{"style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"GIF is not an efficient format. It is recommended to use short MP4 clips instead. See "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/kean\/NukeDemo"},{"type":"text","text":" for an example."}]}],"type":"aside","name":"Note"},{"anchor":"Built-In-Image-Decoders","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Built-In Image Decoders"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can find all of the built-in decoders in the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageDecoders"},{"type":"text","text":" namespace."}]},{"anchor":"ImageDecodersDefault","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"ImageDecoders.Default"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageDecoders\/Default"},{"type":"text","text":" is used by default if no custom decoders are registered. It uses native "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UIImage(data:)"},{"type":"text","text":" (and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NSImage(data:)"},{"type":"text","text":") initializers to create images from data."}]},{"style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When working with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UIImage"},{"type":"text","text":", the decoder automatically sets the scale of the image to match the scale of the screen."}]}],"type":"aside","name":"Note"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The default "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageDecoders\/Default"},{"type":"text","text":" also supports progressively decoding JPEG. It produces a new preview every time it encounters a new frame."}]},{"anchor":"ImageDecodersVideo","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"ImageDecoders.Video"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Generates a video preview and attaches downloaded data to the image container."}]},{"anchor":"ImageDecodersEmpty","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"ImageDecoders.Empty"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageDecoders\/Empty"},{"type":"text","text":" returns an empty placeholder image and attaches image data to the image container. It could also be configured to return partially downloaded data. "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageDecoders\/Empty"},{"type":"text","text":" can be used when the rendering engine works directly with image data."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/nuke\/image-decoding"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/image-decoding","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"article","metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","title":"Image Decoding","role":"article","modules":[{"name":"Nuke"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/com